During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki announced that Dr. Anthony Fauci would be joining her to give an update on the Omicron variant of COVID-19. Dr. Fauci confirmed that the first case of the Omicron variant had been detected in the United States in an individual who had recently traveled from South Africa. The individual was fully vaccinated and experienced mild symptoms that were improving. Dr. Fauci emphasized the importance of getting vaccinated and boosted, as well as other mitigation measures such as mask-wearing and getting children vaccinated. He also stated that it was too early to draw conclusions about the severity and transmissibility of the Omicron variant, but more information would be available in the coming weeks. Dr. Fauci answered questions from reporters regarding testing requirements, travel bans, and the potential for new vaccine requirements. Psaki also addressed other topics such as the President's briefing on the abortion case before the Supreme Court, efforts to cut down on container wait times at ports, and the administration's commitment to ending the HIV epidemic. The briefing concluded with Psaki answering questions about gas prices, Russia's potential invasion of Ukraine, and the President's messaging around vaccines and boosters.